{
  "texts": [
    "At this order, O 7 is the only operator contributing to b → sγ.",
    "The renormalization group evolution to the scale µ b ≃ O(m b) also involves the magnetic gluon penguin operator O 8 and the operators O 1,...6.",
    "Their mixing into O 7 generates large logarithms producing a strong enhancement of the rates.",
    "The anomalous dimension matrix governing the mixing is regularization scheme dependent.",
    "One can get rid of such a dependence defining an effective coefficient C (0)eff 7 (µ b) which includes contributions of O 1,...6 [36]."
  ]
}